name: plantitas and plantitos
description: Plants🌷🌷 are mainly multicellular, predominantly photosynthetic🌻🌻 eukaryotes of the kingdom 🇬🇧🇬🇧 Plantae. They form the clade Viridiplantae (Latin for "green 🤢 plants") that includes the flowering 🌱🌱 plants, conifers and other gymnosperms, ferns, clubmosses, hornworts, liverworts, mosses 🍃and the green 🤢🤢 algae, and excludes the red 👹 and brown 🐴🐴 algae. Historically, plants🌱🌱 were treated as one 1️⃣1️⃣ of two ✌✌ kingdoms🇲🇷🇲🇷 including all living things that were not animals🐒🐒, and all algae and fungi🌲 were treated as plants. However, all current definitions of Plantae 🌲🌲exclude the fungi and some algae, as well as the prokaryotes (the archaea and bacteria🐞🐞)
